  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Citizen-State Relations in Central Mali</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inclusive dialogue at the regional level leads to a common understanding on key security issues and the identification of conflict sensitive responses</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The existing regional forums will be supported with a particular focus on gender issues. In Mopti, the existing local forums of Konna and Djenn? (Mopti region) in the light the MINUSMA and PSOP ? funded security governance project will get along with the regional forum activities to maintain the dialogue sessions at local level as well. In Segou, the local forums of Diabaly and Molodo (Niono Commune, Segou region) will be covered by the project as well. Both local and regional fora members will be drawn from the communities, traditional and community leaders, state authorities? representatives, law enforcement representatives, security and defense forces representatives, and civil society actors.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">There will be a participation of 30% young people and 40% female in all project activities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will promote a common understanding of the forums? members on key security issues and the identification of conflict-sensitive responses at the regional level and contribute to reducing the threat from criminality, political and extremist violence in the regions of Segou and Mopti in Mali.</narrative>
  </description>
